

# Flowchart of each given APIs

1.   `ListActiveCamera`        

#### Shell commands to check the list of available device Manually
To list all video devices picked up by the kernel

    ls -ltrh /dev/video*
    
OR        
    
    v4l2-ctl --list-devices  

To list all devices attached to USB use         
    
    lsusb

2.  `ReadCameraSettings`

#### Shell Commands to check the settings manually

U can vary /dev/videoX , by inserting different values of **X** according to which Device u want to use     
For eg.


    sudo v4l2-ctl --device=/dev/video0 --all
